-- Citigroup Hires Morgan Stanley’s Nick Gray for Credit Trading
-- B y   P a t r i c i a   K u o
-- 2012-08-02T14:30:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-02/citigroup-hires-morgan-stanley-s-nick-gray-for-credit-trading.html
Citigroup Inc. (C)  hired Nick Gray from
Morgan Stanley as a senior credit trader in London.  Gray will join as a director, reporting to Phil Gee, head
of investment-grade credit trading, according to Edwina Frawley-
Gangahar, a Citigroup spokeswoman in London.  Citigroup has been expanding its credit trading business in
Europe. It hired Bjoern Wiegelmann from Deutsche Bank AG and
Nicolas Dujols from Capula Investment Services for the group,
the New York-based bank said in June.  Gray joined Morgan Stanley in 2009. Before that he was with
HSBC Holdings Plc, Barclays Plc and Bank of America Corp.,
according to the Financial Services Authority’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patricia Kuo in  London  at 
